00:45:37.781 --> 00:45:43.062
of of like task completion or task correctness.

00:45:43.062 --> 00:45:48.901
So I'd say, like, generally, if you are working on some kind of analysis, one thing that you

00:45:48.901 --> 00:45:53.141
might want to ask yourself is, like, can you verify it or like, how will you know if it

00:45:53.141 --> 00:45:53.862
is correct?

00:45:53.862 --> 00:45:59.461
If you're doing something with AI and you have no clear answer for how you would tell

00:45:59.461 --> 00:46:02.982
if it's correct or not, you might want to be wary of using it.

00:46:02.982 --> 00:46:04.021
So an example is like.

00:46:06.581 --> 00:46:07.081
Like.

00:46:08.821 --> 00:46:14.581
Analysis where you don't understand if the code or if the data is correct or not.

00:46:16.261 --> 00:46:20.102
And you're asking the LM to tell you if the data is correct.

00:46:20.102 --> 00:46:24.581
It's not going to know that because unless it has access to tons and tons of context.

00:46:26.581 --> 00:46:30.661
And so you might want to be wary or just like use something with more human involvement.

00:46:33.221 --> 00:46:37.542
And then the other thing, a couple other things you might want to ask yourself is also like,

00:46:37.542 --> 00:46:38.821
how much does this thing matter?

00:46:38.821 --> 00:46:41.622
It is very important and hard to verify.

00:46:41.622 --> 00:46:48.982
You might not want to use AI or be wary or cautious or go over the results carefully.

00:46:50.341 --> 00:46:54.581
And then the other final thing is like, are current LLMs good at this type of task?

00:46:54.581 --> 00:47:00.742
Generally, they are very good at, you know, pure coding tasks for most purposes.

00:47:02.102 --> 00:47:03.862
But they are worse at something.

00:47:03.862 --> 00:47:08.742
So like if you are doing some kind of task, you should have a general sense of if LLMs

00:47:08.742 --> 00:47:09.862
are good at that or not.

00:47:09.862 --> 00:47:12.341
And they are really good at some things and less good at others.

00:47:13.221 --> 00:47:16.742
And so it's not sort of a blanket like they are bad at all of data science or they are

00:47:16.742 --> 00:47:17.862
good at all of data science.

00:47:17.862 --> 00:47:23.221
They are good at, you know, sort of different types of tasks or different areas.

00:47:24.341 --> 00:47:24.581
Okay.

