00:47:56.102 --> 00:48:01.701
about your data than it would otherwise have, which can help prevent it from, like, you

00:48:01.701 --> 00:48:09.542
know, hallucinating column names that don't exist or using a column that you don't want

00:48:09.542 --> 00:48:10.102
it to use.

00:48:10.341 --> 00:48:13.701
You might have data where there's two columns that kind of do the same thing.

00:48:13.701 --> 00:48:15.221
You only want it to use one.

00:48:15.221 --> 00:48:21.942
This kind of information could go in the data bot.md file and could save you from creating

00:48:21.942 --> 00:48:23.622
an analysis that is incorrect.

00:48:24.261 --> 00:48:31.942
The other thing is that if it's possible to add, like, determinism in this sort of largely

00:48:31.942 --> 00:48:34.261
non-deterministic process, that can be really helpful.

